Key Match Events: England without key players like Butler, Bairstow, Stokes, and Morgan still defeated West Indies.
Motie had the best bowling figures and best economy in his only game for West Indies on a high-scoring pitch.
Post-Match Reflections: There are calls for Phil Simmonds to be dismissed due to West Indies' poor performance.
West Indies' inability to defeat an English B team in their own backyard has led to criticism.
Others: Discussion on the selection choices, including the dropping of Motie despite his good performance and the persistence with Hayden Walsh despite poor recent stats.
Mention of Royston Chase's recent poor form in both bowling and batting.
Surprise at the selectors not considering Hemraj, who performed well in CPL and Abu Dhabi T10.
